Module io.jstach.ezkv.kvs
Package io.jstach.ezkv.kvs

Interface KeyValuesServiceProvider

All Known Subinterfaces:
KeyValuesMedia, KeyValuesServiceProvider.KeyValuesFilter, KeyValuesServiceProvider.KeyValuesLoaderFinder, KeyValuesServiceProvider.KeyValuesMediaFinder, KeyValuesServiceProvider.KeyValuesProvider
All Known Implementing Classes:
DotEnvKeyValuesMedia, JSON5KeyValuesMedia, XMLKeyValuesMedia
public sealed interface KeyValuesServiceProvider permits KeyValuesServiceProvider.KeyValuesProvider, KeyValuesServiceProvider.KeyValuesLoaderFinder, KeyValuesServiceProvider.KeyValuesFilter, KeyValuesServiceProvider.KeyValuesMediaFinder
A service provider interface (SPI) for extending ezkv's capabilities to support additional media types and URI patterns. Implementations of this interface can be loaded using ServiceLoader.

This SPI allows customization and extension of ezkv's loading mechanisms and media type parsing.

Note: This interface is sealed, and any sub-interface implementations must be registered using provides KeyValuesServiceProvider with ... in the module-info.java or as entries in the META-INF/services/io.jstach.ezkv.kvs.KeyValuesServiceProvider file. Sub-interfaces such as KeyValuesServiceProvider.KeyValuesLoaderFinder and KeyValuesServiceProvider.KeyValuesMediaFinder should not be directly referenced in the service registration.

Example use cases include adding support for custom media types or integrating specialized URI loading logic.

  • Field Details

    • BUILTIN_ORDER_START

      static final int BUILTIN_ORDER_START
      The start order of the builtin components. The start order is low enough that all the builtin components will be less than 0 on purpose to avoid accidental override.
      See Also:
      • Constant Field Values

  • Method Details

    • order

      default int order()
      Since the service providers follow a "resolver" or "finder" pattern order of the providers matters.

      Higher values are interpreted as lower priority. As a consequence, the provider with the lowest value has the highest priority (analogous to Spring's Ordered interface).

      Canonically the builtin components start at -127 so if one is looking to override they should use a lower value.
      Returns:
      by default 0
      See Also:
      • BUILTIN_ORDER_START
